      • requestRelayout

        void requestRelayout​(EditorCell_Collection editorCells)
        Used to notify CellLayout that re-layout of corresponding EditorCell_Collection was requested.

        Can be used to include additional (child) cells into re-layout process by calling EditorCell.requestRelayout() method on corresponding cells.

        Parameters:
        editorCells - EditorCell_Collection to re-layout

      • move

        void move​(EditorCell_Collection editorCells,
          int deltaX,
          int deltaY)
        Used to notify CellLayout that EditorCell.moveTo(int, int) of corresponding EditorCell_Collection was performed.

        Can be used to trigger re-layout for some child cells if layout logic depends on cell x/y coordinates.

        Parameters:
        editorCells - EditorCell_Collection to re-layout
        deltaX - change of X-coordinate (newX - oldX) for editorCells
        deltaY - change of Y-coordinate (newY - oldY) for editorCells
